[normal]Written evidence from[bold] Hampshire County Council[bold] (TIC 070)[bold]Hampshire is a large county
[normal] – 3,700 square kilometres with a population of 1.3 million. It is 85% rural, yet 77% of the population live in
[normal] the
[normal] 
[normal]urban
[normal] areas.
[normal] 
[normal]Car ownership and journey to work length are above the national average reducing opportunities for public transport.  
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Against
[normal] this background, Hampshire County Council has 
[normal]developed
[normal] a range of transport initiatives, training and community engagement 
[normal]programmes
[normal] and 
[normal]has 
[normal]participated in national projects
[normal]. The opportunity to respond to the Committee is welcomed.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]For simplicity, we 
[normal]have provided responses 
[normal]against
[normal] the questions posed by the Committee. We will be happy to clarify or expand any answer if required.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]1.1
[normal] 
[normal]In our countywide review of passenger transport over the period 2006-2009 we 
[normal]combined a wide range of
[normal] existing data including c
[normal]ensus information as to age, car ownership and income, DfT Accession software showing acce
[normal]ss by public transport
[normal] and on foot 
[normal] to key amenities, on-bus surveys of passenger travel patterns, journey purpose, age and ethnicity and modal split information. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]1.2
[normal] 
[normal]Nonetheless, the people who understand local needs best are the elected Members and the 
[normal]local community
[normal], so Hampshire has established a network of parish transport representatives and holds annua
[normal]l passenger transport forums  for
[normal] each district. These have a membership of 1,900 representing a wide range of community groups and organisations. Th
[normal]e
[normal] forums
[normal] are an essential part of 
[normal]gaining information about local issues
[normal] and
[normal] 
[normal]developing
[normal] and testing
[normal] transport options
[normal].
